page.title: 11BIRDS IN THE SAMPFORDS
page.content: The most common birds in The Sampfords are Sparrows and Wood Pigeons. A Kingfisher has been every year near the River Pant but it has not been seen this year as yet. The most beautiful birds in The Sampfords are the Kingfisher, the Mallard Drake and the Cock Pheasant. The biggest bird is the Grey Heron. In the woods are Tawny Owls. Barn Owls are quite rare but there are some around. Also in the woods there is a Nightingale. This has been heard by the village people. There have been two rare visitors. These are the Reed Bunting and the Coal Tit. They came for the food we put out daily.
